##  Version 2.3 Release — ROOT Branch Selector & Enhanced Features

###  Major New Features

#### ROOT Branch Selector Dialog ✨
- **Interactive TTree Browser**: Browse and select TTree branches from ROOT files
- **Multi-select Branches**: Ctrl+click to select multiple numeric branches at once
- **Smart Entry Range Control**: Specify maximum entries to load (defaults to min(50000, total) for responsive performance)
- **Histogram Auto-loading**: Load TH1/TH2/TH3 histograms directly as tabular data
- **Direct GUI Integration**: Loaded data flows into the main GUI's ColumnData system — Add Plot works perfectly on ROOT files now

#### Full ROOT File Integration
- New "Load ROOT to GUI..." button in file panel
- ROOT TTree branches load directly into plot configuration workflow
- 1D/2D/3D histogram creation from TTree data
- Support for histogram extraction (TH1/TH2/TH3 all variants)
- Entry limiting prevents memory bloat on large files

#### Script Panel (From v2.0)
- **Multi-line Script Editor**: Write and execute complete ROOT/C++ or Python scripts
- **Command Line Interface**: Single-line command execution for quick operations
- **Output Viewer**: Separate tab for viewing script output with stream redirection
- **File Operations**: Load and save scripts with auto-language detection

#### Dual Language Support (From v2.0)
- Execute ROOT/C++ macros and code
- Run Python scripts with full ROOT bindings
- Easy language switching

#### Enhanced ROOT File Support (From v2.0)
- ROOT files now open directly in TBrowser
- Full access to all ROOT file objects
- Interactive file exploration
- **NEW:** Load TTree branches into main plotting workflow

