###  Usage Example

**Loading TTree Data:**
```
1. Click "Load ROOT to GUI..."
2. Browse → select mydata.root
3. Dialog shows: Objects [events] [h_mass] ...
4. Select "events" TTree → branches list shows [Pt] [Eta] [Phi] ...
5. Ctrl+click to select [Pt] [Eta] [Phi], set max entries = 50000
6. Click "Load into GUI"
7. Success message: "Loaded: 3 columns × 50000 rows"
8. "Add Plot..." button now ENABLED
9. Configure TH2D(Pt vs Eta), create plot with COLZ option
10. Add another plot: TH1D(Pt), apply Gaussian fit
11. Done! Full plotting pipeline on ROOT TTree data
```

###  Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/siddharthparashri5/Advance_ROOT_Plotting.git
cd Advance_ROOT_Plotting
mkdir -p build && cd build
cmake ..
make -j$(nproc)
./AdvancedPlotGUIApp
```

